lines.text: when will i see you again?
not a single word was said
no final kiss to seal any seam
i had no idea of the state we were in.
i know i have a fickle heart
and a heaviness in my head
the reason you loved me before,
or have you completely erased me
but i know i have a fickle heart
and a heaviness in my head
the reason you loved me before,
and hope that you find the missing piece,
to bring you back to me,
the reason you loved me before,
when will i see you again?

paragraphs.text: when will i see you again? you left with no goodbye, not a single word was said no final kiss to seal any seam i had no idea of the state we were in.
i know i have a fickle heart and a bitterness and a wandering eye, and a heaviness in my head
but don't you remember, don't you remember? the reason you loved me before, baby please remember me once more.
when was the last time you thought of me? or have you completely erased me from your memories? i often think about where i went wrong, the more i do, the less i know
but i know i have a fickle heart and a bitterness and a wandering eye, and a heaviness in my head
but don't you remember, don't you remember? the reason you loved me before, baby please remember me once more.
gave you the space so you could breathe, i kept my distance so you would be free, and hope that you find the missing piece, to bring you back to me,
why don't you remember, don't you remember? the reason you loved me before, baby please remember me once more. when will i see you again?
